Subject: [PATCH] nsswitch.conf.5: mention that "sss" can be used as source for
 compat pseudo-databases

---
 man-pages/man5/nsswitch.conf.5 | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/man-pages/man5/nsswitch.conf.5 b/man-pages/man5/nsswitch.conf.5
index c46175c..56868c3 100644
--- a/man-pages/man5/nsswitch.conf.5
+++ b/man-pages/man5/nsswitch.conf.5
@@ -247,12 +247,16 @@ and
 If this is not sufficient, the NSS `compat' service provides full
 +/\- semantics.
 By default, the source is `nis', but this may be
-overridden by specifying `nisplus' as source for the pseudo-databases
+overridden by specifying any NSS service except `compat' itself
+as the source for the pseudo-databases
 .BR passwd_compat ,
 .B group_compat
 and
 .BR shadow_compat .
 These pseudo-databases are only available in GNU C Library.
+.LP
+If SSSD is installed on your system, you can use `sss' as the source
+for these pseudo-databases.
 .SH FILES
 A service named SERVICE is implemented by a shared object library named
 .BI libnss_SERVICE.so. X
